dev.jeka.core.api.depmanagement

Class JkArtifactId

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.jeka.core.api.depmanagement.JkArtifactId

  • public final class JkArtifactId
extends java.lang.Object
    Artifacts are files produced by projects in order to be published and reused by other projects. JkArtifactId identifies artifacts within a project.

    The identifier is compound of a name and a file extension. The name maps with the Maven 'classifier' concept.
    In a project, we distinguish the main artifact from the others : the main artifact name values to null.

      • of

        public static JkArtifactId of(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.String extension)
        Creates an artifact file id with the specified classifier and getExtension. Both can be null.
        A null or empty classifier generally means the main artifact.
        A getExtension or empty getExtension generally means that the file has no getExtension.
